    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a heavy emphasis on exploiting favorable matchups against weak arms, led by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Josh Naylor** (74.15). **Mickey Moniak** projects as our premier start; batting second against Ryan Weiss provides a massive leverage point, bolstered by a 14% dynamic platoon boost and the favorable park conditions associated with this matchup. Similarly, **Josh Naylor** is in a prime position to capitalize on Walker Buehler\u2019s high 5.19 xERA. We are also leaning into the volume potential of **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.71), both of whom benefit from positive park factors and favorable matchups against K. Montero and Leiter, respectively. These four anchors provide the high-ceiling production necessary to keep our Roto standings competitive.\n\nOur strategy for stolen bases remains aggressive, even in marginal matchups. **Jose Caballero** (70.59) is a must-start despite his lower order position; his 13% platoon edge against Suter, paired with the wind blowing out, creates an environment where he can manufacture both speed and counting stats. While **James Wood** (53.92) fell into our marginal scoring tier, his elite sprint speed remains critical to our scarcity goals; we are prioritizing his inclusion despite the moderate challenge of facing B. Ashcraft. **Kyle Karros** (50.20) represents the closest call on our bench threshold today. While he carries a decent score due to the matchup against Ryan Weiss, he sits at the bottom of our active lineup because his basement-tier order spot negates his potential for RBI accumulation. We continue to monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" tags for **Luis Campusano** and **Mickey Moniak**; should their projected spots shift downward, we may need to re-evaluate our pinch-hit contingencies from our deep bench of **Corbin Carroll**, **Trevor Story**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **Austin Riley**, **Max Muncy**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Travis Bazzana**.",
